<div class="privacy container">
    <h1 class="privacy title">Privacy Policy for Movie Manager</h1>

    <h2 class="privacy section-title">Effective Date: 24/06/2023</h2>

    <p>Thank you for using Movie Manager. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of information collected, how it is used, and how it is protected when you interact with the Movie Manager web application. As the developer, I am committed to maintaining your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information.</p>

    <h3 class="privacy section-title">1. Information Collected</h3>

    <h4>1.1 Personal Information</h4>
    <p>When creating or editing a movie, the only data collected is the text entered by the user. This may include movie titles, descriptions, release dates, and any other relevant information necessary for managing the movie collection. No personally identifiable information (PII) such as names, email addresses, or contact information is collected or stored.</p>

    <h4>1.2 Usage Data</h4>
    <p>Movie Manager may collect non-personally identifiable information about your usage of the application. This includes but is not limited to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Device information (e.g., device type, operating system)</li>
        <li>IP address</li>
        <li>Browser type and version</li>
        <li>Date and time of access</li>
        <li>Pages visited within the application</li>
        <li>Actions performed within the application</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="privacy section-title">2. Use of Information</h3>

    <h4>2.1 Personal Information</h4>
    <p>The text entered when creating or editing a movie is used solely for the purpose of managing your movie collection within the Movie Manager application. Your personal information will not be shared with any third parties, nor will it be used for marketing or advertising purposes.</p>

    <h4>2.2 Usage Data</h4>
    <p>Usage data is collected to improve the performance, functionality, and user experience of Movie Manager. The information may be used for analytics, tracking application usage trends, and identifying and resolving technical issues. Usage data is analyzed in an aggregated and anonymous manner, and no personally identifiable information is associated with it.</p>

    <h3 class="privacy section-title">3. Data Security</h3>

    <h4>3.1 Protection Measures</h4>
    <p>As the developer, I take the security of your data seriously and implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to safeguard it. Movie Manager uses industry-standard security measures to protect against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction of your personal information.</p>

    <h4>3.2 Data Retention</h4>
    <p>Your personal information entered for movie management purposes is stored in an SQLite database hosted on Azure. The data is retained only for as long as it is necessary to fulfill the purpose of managing your movie collection within the application.</p>

    <h3 class="privacy section-title">4. Third-Party Services</h3>

    <h4>4.1 External Links</h4>
    <p>Movie Manager may contain links to external websites or services that are not operated by me. Please note that this Privacy Policy applies only to Movie Manager, and I have no control over the privacy practices of these third-party websites or services. I encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party websites or services before providing any personal information.</p>

    <h3 class="privacy section-title">5. Children's Privacy</h3>
    <p>Movie Manager is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. I do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. If you believe that your child has provided personal information, please contact me, and I will promptly remove such information from our records.</p>

    <h3 class="privacy section-title">6. Changes to the Privacy Policy</h3>
    <p>I reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes made will be effective immediately upon posting the revised Privacy Policy on the Movie Manager website. It is your responsibility to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about any updates or changes.</p>

    <h3 class="privacy section-title">7. Contact Information</h3>
    <p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or the handling of your personal information, please contact me at <b>cal.grimes@outlook.com</b>. I will make reasonable efforts to address your inquiries and resolve any issues in a timely manner.</p>

    <p>By using Movie Manager, you signify your acceptance of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with the terms outlined in this policy, please do not use the application.</p>
</div>
